      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 7,
      "message": "Use present-tense, imperative-style for the 1st line of a commit message. Followed by a blank line. The blank line ensures that the commit message is appropriately parsed for the summary line.\n\nPersonally I think a commit message like this would be better:\n\n Add Casablanca release for sonar & clm\n\nI'd recommend getting familiar with the 7 rules of well formed commit messages:\n\nhttps://chris.beams.io/posts/git-commit/#seven-rules",
